Package: navreport
Type: Package
Title: Multi-Level Navigation R Markdown Template with Lazy Chart Loading
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Diego", "Analista", email = "autor@correo.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides an R Markdown output format that renders HTML documents
    with an unlimited-depth sidebar navigation, lazy-loaded interactive charts,
    and a professional academic/business aesthetic. Supports highcharter,
    plotly, echarts4r, and ggplot2 (via ggplotly). Charts are deferred until
    the user navigates to their page, enabling documents with hundreds of
    charts to open in under 10 seconds.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    rmarkdown (>= 2.20),
    htmltools (>= 0.5.5),
    jsonlite (>= 1.8.0),
    knitr (>= 1.40)
Suggests:
    highcharter (>= 0.9.4),
    plotly (>= 4.10.0),
    echarts4r (>= 0.4.4),
    ggplot2 (>= 3.4.0),
    DT (>= 0.26),
    dplyr
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
